{center}
{subhead}Dr. Strange, Web Wanderer{def}{p}
Article by Mark Tierno
{left}
{pp}
Well, I have enough extra sites stored up for about three more months
of web Wanderer, but only just this one time left.  Hmm, well there's
only one thing to do... squeeze in as many of these pesky little things
as I can.  Enjoy the last Web Wanderer.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}World Is Round{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.worldisround.com{noitalic}{p}
Get a look at places around the world through the pictures submitted
by other people just like you.  There's even a couple from Antarctica.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Roadside America{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.roadsideamerica.com/{noitalic}{p}
See offbeat roadside attractions along the highways and byways of
America, including sauch features as the world's largest fire hydrant,
a rattlesnake ranch, the dinosaur gardens, and a whole lotofother odd
things.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}On This Day{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.on-this-day.com/{noitalic}{p}
On this day in history... Wll, you can read about it at this site. 
Events big and small, birthdays, and what-not listed for any given
day or just do a search for a specified day.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}So You Wanna{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.soyouwanna.com/{noitalic}{p}
So you wanna... learn to playpoker, be a model, buy a cell phone,
donate to charity, mix drinks, flatten your abs, throw a bacheleor
party, be a sitcom writer,...  Well, you get the idea.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Saute' Wednesday{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.sautewednesday.com/{noitalic}{p}
Pretty basic layout but if you like cooking recipies and other
food-content related links and stuff then this is a good place to
start.
{pp}
{pp}              
{bold}Rotten Tomatoes{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.rottentomatoes.com/{noitalic}{p}
Another movie review site with a theme, this one comparing rotten
movies to tomatoes of the same kind.  A scale that goes from rotten to
fresh by taking a summary of reviews from several other reviewers
(papers, TV, etc.), all of which you can read right there for
yourself.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Amiga Remix{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.amigaremix.com/{noitalic}{p}
Need a good place to look for all the best Amiga remixes?  Try here.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Interactive Plasma Physics Experience{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://ippex.pppl.gov/{noitalic}{p}
To parapgrase the site's own description, thisplace contains
Interactive Plasma Physics Topics, ranging from electricity,
magnetism, energy, and fusion.  If you're into science then check it
out.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Googlism{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.googlism.com/{noitalic}{p}
Enter in a person, place, or thing and this will tell you what Google
thinks of it...  According to this, apparently I am a bird.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}W3C Link Checker{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://validator.w3.org/checklink{noitalic}{p}
A handy little online utility to check the validity of web links. 
Just enter in the URL and it'll spit out the info.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Dr. Strange's Homepage{nobold}
{italic}http://members.tripod.com/~dr-strange{noitalic}{p}
Okay, so I couldn't leave you without posting my own homepage, just
in case anyone wants to get a look at me.  Remember to check out the
writing and philosophy links.
{pp}
{pp}
{center}{bold}Pick Of The Month{nobold}{left}
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Linky And dinky Find The Darndest Links{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.linkydinky.com{noitalic}{p}
Well, just so as to not leave  you in a lurch in your monthly search
for useful, fun, and bizarre sites, here's one of the few links sites
I'dactually write a review about.  Each month Linky and Dinky search
out the web and bring you the bestof the strange.
{pp}
Need examples?  Amazing Contraption has an implausible Rube Goldberg
device, Iraqi Treasures, Need A Load For A Boob Job?, Secret DVD
Features, Moon any website, and a whole lot more.  If you want anymore
details on some of these sites then you'll just have to go down to
Linky and Dinky's and read up about it.
{pp}
{pp}
Well, that's all... period.  This is Dr. Strange taking his bow...
{pp}

